The paper deals with modeling uncertain information and decision making, which are common topics in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper specifically addresses the limitations of the Dempster-Shafer evidence theory, which is a well-known method in the field of decision making and uncertainty modeling (cs.DS). The paper also introduces a new theory and presents a combination rule, which are related to information theory (cs.IT) and signal processing (cs.SI).
